The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, gave a press briefing where he discussed a range of topics including the ongoing negotiations with Iran, the President's upcoming visit to a federal prison, criminal justice reform, and the commutation of sentences for 46 non-violent drug offenders. Earnest stated that progress has been made in the Iran negotiations, but there are still sticking points that need to be resolved. He also mentioned that the President is open to bipartisan conversations on criminal justice reform and that the commutations are part of the President's efforts to make the criminal justice system more fair.